# TSan suppressions for known-safe races inside SQLite's amalgamation.
#
# SQLite's WAL implementation coordinates cross-connection access to the
# *-shm file via OS file locks and a checksum-validated read-with-retry
# protocol — not via in-process mutexes. TSan can't model that and reports
# the lock-free shared-memory reads/writes as data races. They are not
# bugs; suppressing them lets TSan find real races in our own code
# (sqlite/oro_*.cpp).
#
# Anchor suppressions on SQLite symbol names rather than the full
# sqlite3.c path so they're stable across amalgamation regenerations.

race:walIndexTryHdr
race:walIndexWriteHdr
race:walIndexReadHdr
race:walTryBeginRead
race:walTryBeginWrite
race:walCheckpoint

# Pager-level retry loops also touch shared state without an in-process
# mutex; they're safe for the same reason.
race:pagerBeginReadTransaction
race:sqlite3PagerSharedLock

# Linker/init-time races inside the MOT engine (third_party/oro-db) are
# out of scope for this branch — track separately. Suppress to keep
# motlite-level races surfaceable.
race:libmot
race:MOT::
